Here are some of your comments. Thanks, even to those who send 
me true hate mail, for reading these articles. Also, I am sorry 
for the typo error the other day. Yes, it should have been 
weight instead of wait. 
Denis Mueller 

Just got around to reading your piece on Sharon. 
Unfortunately, being anti-Israel seems to be a prerequisite 
for maintaining one's credentials as a liberal. Certainly, 
Sharon is no dove. You do exaggerate about the numbers at 
Shattila, and your idea that Israel fights the PLO only to 
facilitate annexation of the West Bank is wrongheaded. 

That is like saying that the US fought the Germans so they 
could occupy a slice of Berlin. You also conveniently omit 
the fact that Sharon sends in the tanks when Hamas massacres 
Jews, because it allows them to sabotage the peace process. 
Hamas wants no less than the liquidation of Israel, not peace. 

You also don't mention that Sharon was elected because the 
Israeli's were disgusted with Arafat's rejection of the peace 
settlement that was offered. You allege that Sharon wants to 
drive out the "Palestinians". If he followed the example set 
by Hamas, Israel could have massacred them all by now. The fact 
that Israel has not done so shows that they follow a higher 
moral path than their neighbors. Try to be a little more even-
handed. Otherwise your version of "history" will remain 
forgotten, as it should be. 
BN 

