Hi, Denis; 

Thankfully, today, we can disregard the call-up without fear 
of arrest or raids by federal marshals in the middle of the 
night (at least I hope we don't have to fear that, though the 
Patriot Act and other events seem to indicate otherwise). I 
had to go in, or else, back in 1968 and my family was not 
sufficiently wealthy to find a "legal way" out or fund a trip 
to Canada. President Bush and Vice President Cheney did not 
heed the call-up when their lives and careers were at stake, 
but they most certainly have no problem with calling up a 
younger generation to kill and be killed. 

That's why, like most veterans of my generation, I never voted 
for those bastards and I am actively getting involved with 
current anti-war groups like Move-On.org 
Dan Jacobson - former Hospital Corpsman - served honorably from 
1968 to 1972 
Thank You! Thank You! 

