  ~*~*~*~*~ KOREA - THE FORGOTTEN WAR on video ~*~*~*~*~

For the millions of servicemen who served in Korea, it can 
never be forgotten. It was one of the most hard-fought and 
bloody wars of all time, over 2,000,000 lives were lost, 
including over 33,000 Americans. Now comes this unprecedented 
video that is undoubtedly one of the best videos ever produced
on Korea. This is the most complete record of the war ever 
made -- from the land, air and sea you will see it all unfold 
before your very eyes. The battle footage is gut-wrenching and
the stories unforgettable. Revisit a little known chapter in 
American History. To order for $19.98 (92 minutes) visit: 
	     http://ads.pulsetv.com/al/a?aid=521&ent=26
    <a href="http://ads.pulsetv.com/al/a?aid=521&ent=26">
Order Korea The Forgotten War</a>
------------------------------------------------------------ 

I see Eisenhower as one of the most over looked and under-
estimated presidents we had in the 20th Century. He not only 
gave that speech, but started the ball rolling in Civil Rights 
with his use of federalization of the State National Guard of 
Arkansas to enforce the Supreme Court's overturning of the 
"separate but equal" doctrine (declared separate and unequal) 
that states were using to justify segregation of the races. 
How far would the Civil Rights movement have gotten without 
that first step? Present-day Republicans should take a good 
hard look at what they have left behind in their current 
pursuit of gratifying only the wealthy few. 

Where did you EVER get the idea that J E H was "generally 
thought of as the worst public official" we ever had? Taint; 
true, he is regarded as a homo but did a good job for the 
times in which he lived. I also lived in those times. 

Rev. T Stanton 

